    "body": "### Problem\n\nneovim's markdown formatting when using `gq` breaks triple-backtick code blocks.\n\nStart with a valid markdown file (escaping the triple-backtick here so it can be displayed by github):\n\n```\n# hello\n\n\\```\nhello\nagain\n\\```\n```\n\n`gq` the whole thing:\n\n```\n# hello\n \n``` hello again ```\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nAs described above, clean nvim.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCode blocks should probably be left alone? Their lines definitely shouldn't be merged, the triple-backticks should be left where they are, and wrapping would also breaks stuff.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nDon't have vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nVoid Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nSystem package manager",
